es of ethnic Chinese in nation-building. It brings together a group of established Southeast Asian scholars to critically examine some of the important issues such as ethnic politics, nation-building, state policies, and conflict resolution. These scholars of different ethnic origins present their own ethnic perspectives and hence make the book unique. This is the mostup-to-date book on ethnic/racial relations with special reference to the ethnic Chinese in three Southeast Asian countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aDahana, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHing, Lee Kam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamasamy, P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSer, Tan Ern, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShamsul, A.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiddique, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTan, Eugene K.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTan, Mely G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWinarta, Frans H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Ba